				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I will tell you why people complain about this race....starting stats...Just because our STR is base 70 we get the shaft....I will tell you this, unless your STR is 200+ I really doesnt matter. STA=Hitpoints, the morre the merrier. We have low STA in the beginning. AGI=AC, our AGI is not that high. To all you n00bs who use this as your base I have one word for you...BUFFS. Why else would a shaman have a heap of STR, AGI, STA buff spells? Why would a cleric have a line of HP spells? stats dont mean anything when you become a higher level. there is only one word a hybrid should be concerened with AC. AC is god, AC is king. Know it, love it. Let the shammy's, druid's and cleric's do there damn job. We, we as in Shadow Knights that are Erudites, show our real power at level 39+. Our DoT's and debuffs are mana monsters. Being of a naturally higher INT we can cast these more than most races. But dont let this fool you. I know many trolls with an INT of 120 or so, simply because they focus on this stat. All in all there is no dominate race. It is all in the interest of the player to decide what his character's race will be. If he likes to cast, dont be a troll SK. If he wants to smash stuff, dont be an Erudite paladin. Really now...argueing is useless..and childish<BR>
<BR>
Bellemarr Diesteranum<BR>
43rd Erudite Shadow Knight
