			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here is my story. I think I know what I am doing, because I have had 2 Erudite Wizards. The first, Aaumin, was abandoned at level 5 because of his &quot;low&quot; 120 INT. I will say now-- You MUST max out your int. My second character, Fauste, is a little slower, a little weaker, and has slightly less stamina than Aaumin, but his INT is 142 base, so it's all good. First thing I did with Fauste was to go to Qeynos. I got up to level 2 as I waited around for a teleport. Well, I not only lost my corpse, but I didn't get the tele I was looking for. Fed up with all of the Non-Erudites, I took the ship back to my home, where I immediately got a teleport to Freeport. Trust me here- a lvl 4-12 wizard is a VALUABLE commodity in groups in east commons, simply because they are so rare. I nuked my way through 9 levels, and I am now at level 11, OH SO CLOSE to level 12. <BR>
<BR>
In response, yes I DO believe that Erudites are evil. They are nont evil for the Dark Elves reasons (being sadistic maniacs), but rather they simply know that evil permits more freedom, allowing you to do beneficial things your conscience might not otherwise allow. When asked if I am good or evil (Erudites get that question a lot, it seems) I say ' you chose between neither or both, because both descriptions fit me'<BR>
<BR>
Also, Erudite Wizards are VERY underestimated. Today, a level 11 half elf ranger in east commons was making fun of me, saying that wizards are useless and can't take pain. Naturally, I challenged him to a duel outside of the Tunnel and proceeded to put him away with NO trouble. Since then, the insults to my race/class have been conspicuously absent. Heh, showed them.<BR>
<BR>
If you ever happen to be wandering around on the Tribunal server near Freeport, just send a tell to Fauste, and I will be glad to help you.<BR>
<BR>
Fauste, 11th (I guess I can say 12th now) Erudite Wizard of the Tribunal
