	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Tips about playing an Erud Wiz.<BR>
<BR>
This race has high int but terribly low Agi.  It's horrible soloing an Erud Wiz from levels 1 thru 5.  <BR>
<BR>
But as soon as I made lvl 6, I was able to solo a Kobold Camp and made lvl 9 within 2 hours dying only once.<BR>
<BR>
Things to remember about being an Erud.  You have Tox Forest, one of the most uncomfortable zones in EQ since it's so easy to get lost.  But you do learn alot hanging out there till level 10.  <BR>
<BR>
If you make lvl 10 in Tox, you'll be a master of loc.  You won't fear getting lost and dying in the middle of nowhere.  Just type /loc as you lay unconscious, then have a friend come along to help you retrieve your body.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
