				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Lol, i love it when people get paladins using wis with SK using int mixed up.  Its so funny and they really make themselves look dumb, anyways.  I just started a Erudite SK, ok i know they are weak, stats are only 90/75/70/70/83/117/70. ya, they cant see, and yes they are not that strong, fast or accurate.  But hey, stats aren't everything.  hes pretty damn fun, paineel is a cool city, and they look pretty bad in armor because raelly, ive never even seen a erudite SK or pally on my mage who is 47.  So i just decided to go against the flow and make a erudite.  With velious and a little money, ill be able to buy plenty of stat raising items to buff up my stats, wont have to worry about INT.  im just trying to say that you should not focus on just the race with the best stats, hell if i wanted that i would of made a ogre, but they are huge and fat and i dont like that.  Also i was going to make a troll sk, thinking that the regen would kick ass, but then i remember that post 20, regen doesnt really matter because you are in a group, and they have healers who heal yo ass. so play what you want and be happy
